{
  "texts": [
    "From these data, using a one-sample test of proportions for each question, we have found that the proportion of positive answers is significantly greater than the proportion of negative answers in every case (with p-values that are mostly very low).",
    "This confirms that our system is positively evaluated by the users.",
    "Focusing on the specific questionnaire outlined in Table 6, it is evident the positive impact of explanations when comparing the responses to SQ1 with those of other questions.",
    "Thus, while the recommendations, without the presence of explanations, were initially received positively (51), the counts for other specific questions, which consider the impact of the explanation, increased.",
    "Conversely, the opposite trend is observed for instances of negative responses to SQ1 (17)."
  ]
}